
Overview of verb rive

The verb rive has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) rend, rip, rive, pull -- (tear or be torn violently; "The curtain ripped from top to bottom"; "pull the cooked chicken into strips")
2. cleave, split, rive -- (separate or cut with a tool, such as a sharp instrument; "cleave the bone")
